// useDesignCanvasInput
// Handles all mouse, touch, and gesture input on the design editor canvas via a drag state machine.

Drag states: draw, move, pan, resize, rotate, marquee, pen-drag, text-select.
Mouse drags that start inside the canvas are tracked with window-level listeners so they continue
if the cursor leaves the canvas boundary.
Touch input supports single-finger pan and two-finger pinch-to-zoom.
Safari macOS gesture events (gesturestart/change/end) are also handled for trackpad pinch.

FUNCTION useDesignCanvasInput({ canvasRef, hitTestSectionTitle, hitTestComponentLabel })  EXPORT
  CALLS: computeSelectionBounds (snap), computeSnap (snap), getEditorRefs (designEditorRefs),
         useDesignEditorStore (designEditorStore)
  Registers all canvas event listeners on mount and removes them on unmount.
  Listeners: mousedown (with window capture), mousemove, mouseup, mouseleave, dblclick, wheel,
  touchstart, touchmove, touchend, touchcancel, gesturestart, gesturechange, gestureend, contextmenu.

---

FUNCTION getCoords(e) -> { sx, sy, cx, cy }
  Converts a MouseEvent's client position to canvas-local screen coordinates (sx, sy) and
  canvas/world coordinates (cx, cy) using the current pan and zoom.

---

FUNCTION applyResize(d, cx, cy, constrain)
  Computes new x/y/width/height for the node being resized based on which handle is active and
  the current cursor position relative to the drag start.
  IF constrain (Shift held), maintains the original aspect ratio.
  Clamps width and height to a minimum of 1.

---

FUNCTION computeAutoLayoutIndicatorForFrame(parent, cx, cy)
  Determines where a dragged node would be inserted in an auto-layout frame and updates the
  layout insert indicator in the store with position, index, and orientation.

---

FUNCTION onMouseDown(e)
  Dispatches into the appropriate drag state based on the active tool and what was hit:
  - Middle button or HAND tool: starts pan drag.
  - SELECT tool: checks for text editing, rotation handle, resize handle, or node hit in order.
    On node hit, starts a move drag; Alt+drag duplicates the selection first.
    On empty space, starts a marquee drag.
  - PEN tool: adds a vertex and starts a pen-drag.
  - TEXT tool: creates a text node and enters text editing immediately.
  - Shape tools: creates a new node and starts a draw drag.
  Tracks multi-click count (double/triple) for text selection behavior.

---

FUNCTION onMouseMove(e)
  Updates hover highlight and cursor style when no drag is active.
  Dispatches drag updates based on current drag type:
  - pan: updates panX/panY directly.
  - rotate: computes new angle, snaps to 15° increments if Shift held, updates rotation preview.
  - move: applies snap guides, detects auto-layout drop targets, updates node positions.
  - text-select: updates text cursor position.
  - resize: delegates to applyResize.
  - pen-drag: updates the pen tangent handle.
  - draw: updates node width/height from drag delta; Shift constrains to square.
  - marquee: updates marquee rect and selection from overlapping nodes.

---

FUNCTION onMouseUp()
  Finalizes the drag operation:
  - move: commits move to undo history; reparents nodes if dropped on a frame, or ejects them
    if dragged outside their parent bounds.
  - resize: commits resize to undo history.
  - rotate: applies final rotation and commits to undo history.
  - draw: snaps tiny shapes to 100x100; adopts nodes into sections if applicable; resets tool to SELECT.
  - marquee: clears the marquee rect.
  Clears drag state and resets cursor.

---

FUNCTION onWheel(e)
  Shift+scroll pans the canvas. Plain scroll zooms toward the cursor position.

---

FUNCTION onDblClick(e)
  Deep hit tests the click position. If a TEXT node is hit, enters text editing and selects the
  clicked word. Otherwise selects the deepest node under the cursor.

---

FUNCTION onTouchStart(e)
  Single touch: starts a pan drag. Two touches: records pinch start distance, zoom, and midpoint.

---

FUNCTION onTouchMove(e)
  Two touches: applies pinch-to-zoom centered on the pinch midpoint.
  Single touch with pan drag: updates panX/panY.

---

FUNCTION onTouchEnd(e)
  Clears drag state when all fingers lift. If one finger remains, transitions to a single-finger pan drag.

---

FUNCTION onGestureStart(e)
  Records the current zoom as the baseline for a Safari gesture sequence.

---

FUNCTION onGestureChange(e)
  Applies zoom proportional to the gesture scale, centered on the gesture position.

---

FUNCTION onGestureEnd(e)
  Prevents default to suppress browser handling of the gesture end.

---

FUNCTION onMouseLeave()
  Clears snap guides and hovered node when the cursor leaves the canvas (only when not dragging).

---

FUNCTION onMouseDownWithWindowCapture(e)
  Calls onMouseDown, then if a drag was started, attaches window-level mousemove and one-time
  mouseup listeners so the drag continues outside the canvas boundary.

---

FUNCTION onContextMenu(e)
  Prevents the browser context menu and opens the editor context menu at the cursor position.

---

FUNCTION getScreenRect(absX, absY, w, h, zoom, panX, panY)
  Converts absolute canvas coordinates and dimensions to screen pixel bounds.

---

FUNCTION getHandlePositions(absX, absY, w, h, zoom, panX, panY)
  Returns the eight resize handle positions (nw, n, ne, e, se, s, sw, w) in screen coordinates.

---

FUNCTION unrotate(sx, sy, centerX, centerY, rotation)
  Rotates a screen point back into the unrotated frame of a node, for use in rotated hit tests.

---

FUNCTION hitTestHandle(sx, sy, absX, absY, w, h, zoom, panX, panY, rotation) -> HandlePosition | null
  Returns which resize handle (if any) the cursor is within HANDLE_HIT_RADIUS of, accounting for node rotation.

---

FUNCTION hitTestRotationHandle(sx, sy, absX, absY, w, h, zoom, panX, panY, rotation) -> boolean
  Returns true if the cursor is within ROTATION_HIT_RADIUS of the rotation handle above the node's top edge.
